QuestData.Title: Pulse of the Wharf
QuestData.Description: I am at a loss for ideas, $n. The tides churn, and I can feel their pain as if it is my own.$b$bWhile I am out of ideas, perhaps the merchants in town may have seen something? They are always watching and gossiping, making them quite good sources of information.
QuestData.LogDescription: Talk to Julian Nichols, Ginger Freelin, and Aaron Gutier in Anglepoint Wharf.
QuestData.CompletionText: The merchants here generally have a thumb on the pulse of the wharf. If anybodyпїЅs noticed anything strange in town, its them.
QuestData.RewardText: In the name of the sea! Did you see that?
